# M365 Knowledge Graph — Configuration Example
# ============================================================
# SQLite + LanceDB Backend (Local-First, File-Based)
# No external database or graph services required
# ============================================================

# Database Configuration
# SQLite file path — automatically created if not present
# For Windows: file:///C:/Users/YourUsername/AppData/Local/Cowork GHC/m365kg.db?cache=shared
# For Linux/Mac: file:./m365kg.db?cache=shared
DATABASE_URL=file:./m365kg.db?cache=shared

# Server Configuration
HOST=0.0.0.0
PORT=8080
ENVIRONMENT=development

# Security
JWT_SECRET=your-32-character-or-longer-secret-key-here

# Microsoft 365 Integration (Required for M365 data ingestion)
M365_TENANT_ID=your-azure-tenant-id
M365_CLIENT_ID=your-app-registration-client-id
M365_CLIENT_SECRET=your-app-registration-client-secret
M365_AUTH_MODE=entra_id

# M365 Sync Configuration
DELTA_SYNC_INTERVAL=300  # seconds (default: 5 minutes)

# CORS Configuration
ALLOWED_ORIGINS=http://localhost:5173,http://localhost:3000

# Optional: LLM Service Integration (for embeddings and entity extraction)
# Leave empty to disable embeddings (graceful degradation)
LLMSVC_ADDR=localhost:50051
LLMSVC_TLS=false
LLMSVC_CERT_FILE=

# Optional: OAuth Redirect URI (for Entra ID callback)
OAUTH_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:8080/api/auth/callback

# Optional: Dev Login (development/testing only)
# DEV_LOGIN_USERNAME=dev@example.com
# DEV_LOGIN_PASSWORD=dev-password
# ADMIN_USER_IDS=dev@example.com,admin@example.com

# LLM Model Configuration (if using llm-svc)
LLM_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini
LLM_EMBED_MODEL=text-embedding-3-small

# ============================================================
# Configuration Notes
# ============================================================
#
# 1. DATABASE_URL:
#    - Uses SQLite file-based storage
#    - File created automatically at specified path
#    - WAL mode enabled for concurrent read/write
#    - Use file:/// prefix for absolute paths
#
# 2. JWT_SECRET:
#    - Must be at least 32 characters
#    - Keep this secure in production
#    - Generate: openssl rand -base64 32
#
# 3. M365 Integration:
#    - Requires Azure App Registration
#    - Required scopes:
#      * Files.Read.All (OneDrive/SharePoint)
#      * Chat.Read.All (Teams messages)
#      * Mail.Read (Mailbox content)
#    - See docs/INTEGRATION.md for full scope list
#
# 4. LLMSVC_ADDR (Optional):
#    - Enables embeddings and LLM-based entity extraction
#    - Leave empty to run without LLM features (degraded mode)
#    - Format: "host:port" (e.g., "localhost:50051")
#
# 5. DELTA_SYNC_INTERVAL:
#    - Controls how often M365 is polled for changes
#    - Default: 300 seconds (5 minutes)
#    - Larger values = less frequent sync, lower bandwidth
#
# ============================================================
# Quick Start
# ============================================================
#
# 1. Copy this file to .env:
#    cp .env.example .env
#
# 2. Update with your values:
#    - M365_TENANT_ID
#    - M365_CLIENT_ID
#    - M365_CLIENT_SECRET
#    - JWT_SECRET
#
# 3. Build and run:
#    go build -o m365kg ./cmd
#    ./m365kg
#
# The app will create the SQLite database at DATABASE_URL automatically.
# ============================================================
